```bash
}

)

# Step 3: Add Signature Shares
signature_shares=(
  "f6efd543a9bf33bc2a2f22ea6daea91bffd25f8cb7632d3e2abface392e2224b"
  "34bc08074458011a307319ee5e505c33ae708b4e3c0b65148a6ccf96502a33a6"
  "962de1eedb4cdbe91c7e23e6625e9cc89fb634562f08587f555ac4b5a46f338d"
  "976f900d584d368ea21f6c9aee23e13533a90228805a2e1f1f8eaa175d8440eb"
  "656f490ef5ef6dc02ce00d8821dfceceb422f33df17705d2feac9a0ec00e2687"
  "49bbaeff5ba49f3b82dc58431b8814331f0f76cb33e51afa3e30352212d731b1"
  "7cd23db605acf324bb616b3c2442a2c8e0334ce739e819c78e6ed607939f7523"
  "07262ffb7f0cd0be127415a9d26f98281c763c32f594ec79641aadb5fad52012"
  "46e71f29b64aa80e1c75cd478a00f92320bd96832c12d5f6451128f74b3d4cb0"
  "150f1cb87f3408312bd32ed81eedddcaeec4a0581144ef070593acfe15df78eb"
  "ea3586fa679785157072cbd5aaa8528ec5cb50e4a7de430f560c0baa6eecb1b4"
  "85eea65158f938cee84f340c55a11c30683aa2ef37155f91ba585e2685fe72af"
  "128af70cedc7a2a1ef050f78aa98136669df1e080ce24b52566481bb80329a22"
)

# Loop through the list of signature shares
for i in "${!signature_shares[@]}"; do
  signature_share="${signature_shares[$i]}"

  # Convert index to hexadecimal, starting from 1 (so add 1 to $i)
  signer_id=$(printf "%064x" $(($i + 1)))

  # Create the payload for this signer
  payload=$(cat <<EOF
{
    "round_id": "$round_id",
    "signer_id": "$signer_id",
    "signature_share": "$signature_share"
}
EOF
)

  # Post the request
  curl -X POST "$url/round/$round_id/signature" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d "$payload"

  echo "Posted signature share for signer_id: $signer_id"
done

# Step 4: Get Signature group
curl -X GET $url/round/$round_id/aggregate
```

```rust
// identifier_utils.rs
use frost_secp256k1::{Identifier};
use std::convert::TryFrom;

pub fn identifier_from_hex_string(hex_str: &str) -> Identifier {
    let scalar_value = u16::from_str_radix(hex_str, 16).unwrap();
    Identifier::try_from(scalar_value).unwrap()
}

// Edit from 
let id = Identifier::derive(signer_id.as_bytes())?;
// To
let id = identifier_from_hex_string(&signer_id);
```
